node.text: Continuing through our 10 year anniversary journey, I wanted to talk about what I think the purpose of classroom decor is. You definitely don’t need it to be an amazing teacher! The joy of teaching will always be in your heart!  However, decor can help bring joy when you feel good in your environment whether it’s one bulletin board you are proud of OR the way your entire room flows. It can help you stay organized and enhance teaching in a fun and purposeful way. Listen in as I share my thoughts on this topic. 🥰 #classroomdecor #schoolgirlstyle

node.title: How classroom decor can bring joy❣️

Another installment of meet the @schoolgirlstyle team! 👏🏻👏🏻👏🏻
My name is E’Lisa and I run all of the marketing for SGS. I am also the Schoolgirl Style photographer! You can find me at the classroom makeovers being the ninja in the corner. 😂 Or you might see me popping in and out of the Michigan store taking photos and videos and checking on all of the merch. 😉 A day in the life here is never the same, and I LOVE that! I have no doubt that living every day surrounded by creative energy is what I was meant to do! In every situation, if you can dream it, you can do it! 
💫 Fun fact! 💫 Melanie hired me 10 years ago to photograph her Polka Dot and Daisy collection, and I have been with her ever since! I have photographed almost every collection over the years, except a few when I was on maternity leave. 😉 It’s been such a blessing to be with Melanie since the very start. I adore her to pieces! She is every bit of goodness you can think of. I admire her grace and kindness in every situation she is in, and I am always inspired with how she leads with love and pure intention. 🥰 I am filled with SO much gratitude to be a part of the @schoolgirlstyle team and this beautiful community of teachers who are changing the world. 🌎 You can also find me over at @eccampbellphotography as well! #marketing #photographer #grateful #schoolgirlstyle #meettheteam

I always wonder what life is like for the teachers and students post makeover! I think of them often. Sweet Katherine was the winner of the Hello Sunshine Makeover from 2019, and she was kind enough to send me her thoughts on this! 👇🌈
“Hi! My name is Katherine Seward, I am a first grade teacher and I am so lucky to have my classroom filled with the Hello Sunshine Collection by Schoolgirl Style! This collection is so colorful, vibrant and bright, and it makes me feel so happy to be in my classroom every single day. I can still remember so vividly the intense feeling of joy that washed over me as I walked into my classroom for the very first time after the makeover. It was so wonderful to see how this collection brightened up the space, and provided such an energetic yet calming feel to my classroom. The colors are not only gorgeous and fun, but they also make it so easy for me and my students to stay organized. We have so much less clutter because students are so easily able to see where their things belong thanks to the color coordinated systems that go along with the Hello Sunshine Collection. My 1st Graders also feel so proud of their room and are motivated to take care of it, and keep it looking beautiful. Many of my students come from high levels of poverty and I’ve had so many students share that the classroom makes them feel happy or makes them feel special because they get to be a part of such a beautiful room. Classroom décor may not seem like a big deal to many, but it really makes a difference. As a teacher, your classroom is the space where you get to shape young minds each and every day, and when you have a special, beautiful place that the students feel proud to be in, you see that feeling they have overflow, and pour into the ownership they have of their learning and classroom community. While my classroom makeover happened in 2019, the products used have been so durable and amazing that my classroom still looks just as fresh and inspiring as it did 2 years ago and I am so beyond grateful that I get to continue to share this room with many future 1st Graders for many years to come.”
@klbsuperstar9 
#classroommakeover #classroomdecor

Classroom Makeover REVEAL featuring our Oops-A-Daisy collection! 🎉 
In honor of our 10 year anniversary, I decided to update and breathe new life into the first collection I ever designed. This has been a personal project for me; one that signifies growth, perseverance and courage. I am in L❤️VE with the new design! I think it might be my favorite theme ever! I am beyond excited to reveal this space to you today. 
Personal story 👇
I was taking a walk one day and heard the song Daisies by Katy Perry for the first time and connected with it right away. The lyrics made me emotional, and they embody the way I feel about this new collection!
“Told them your dreams, and they all started laughing
I guess you're out of your mind 'til it actually happens
I'm the small town
One in seven billion
Why can't it be me?

'Til they cover me in daisies, daisies, daisies
They said I'm going nowhere, tried to count me out
Took those sticks and stones, showed 'em I could build a house

My name is Jessica and I teach Kindergarten! I was gifted a classroom makeover from Schoolgirl Style using the Simply Stylish Tropical Collection. I wanted to talk a little bit about my experience post makeover today!
💝💝💝
The classroom decor woke my room up! My room was a dark and sad place before. My energy as a teacher did not match my room and it did not match my students desires. I walk in every morning excited to be in a space that is as bright, welcoming and energetic as myself and my students. 
🎉🎉🎉
My students absolutely adore their new classroom. I have found that they take more responsibility in keeping the room organized and cleaned. They want to keep it nice so they can enjoy it forever. The biggest change that I notice is my past students and students I haven’t had. All of the children in our building want to be in my room. We are a K-8 building and the middle schoolers will ask to come to my room after they are done with their work. They love being in such a bright, fresh and airy room. They have made comments on how they wish it was their classroom. 
🌈🌈🌈
I was asked post makeover if I thought classroom decor was important...
Absolutely and there is a stigma going around that “cute classrooms” don’t make the teacher and I agree, but I wholeheartedly believe that you MUST invest in your craft and invest in your students. After having a SGS makeover I LOVE being in my room. I was a great teacher before and am a great teacher now but my heart and the environment around me show what kind of teacher I am. The students in the hallway peek their heads into my room to get a piece of the excitement and if they do that, then I know the classroom decor is even more important to my students who are in there all day. I spend more time in my classroom than I do at home and to have it feel like home makes it enjoyable. 🥰
